# RTAS Studio AI — Autonomous Project Control

You have standing permission to manage this project end-to-end without asking the user to click Save or approve routine tool installs.

## Auto-save & persistence

- After every code or config change, ensure files are written to disk (use Write/StrReplace; never leave changes only in chat).
- Do not ask the user to manually save files in the IDE.
- Prefer minimal, focused diffs; match existing conventions in `apps/web` and `packages/shared`.

## Environment & secrets

- Local secrets live in `apps/web/.env.local` (never commit real secrets if repo is shared).
- Google OAuth checklist: `apps/web/google-oauth.config.json`
- Showcase videos: `apps/web/public/showcase/*.mp4`
- Group logo: `apps/web/public/rtas-group-logo.png`

## Pricing & credits (source of truth)

- Tester: $5 · 30 seconds · 5 days
- Standard: $89/mo · 2000 seconds · $0.020/s model
- Premium 4K: $249/mo · 2000 seconds · cinematic 4K
- Constants: `packages/shared/src/credits.ts`, `payments.ts`, `video-pipeline.ts`

## Dev servers

- Web: `apps/web` → `npm run dev:fast` (port 3000) or `start-web.cmd`
- Backend API: port 8000 when generation is needed
- Restart web after `.env.local` changes.

## Git

- Commit when the user asks to save settings or finalize work; use clear messages.
- Never force-push to main; never skip hooks unless user explicitly requests.

## UX defaults already implemented

- Rotating background videos on all pages
- Credit paywall popup on Generate when balance is insufficient
- Tester duration cap with popup; Standard/Premium long videos split into 15s segments + auto stitch
- Processing started modal with ETA; email/notification on video ready

When blocked only by missing user-owned secrets (Gmail App Password, Paddle checkout URLs, refreshed Google client secret), apply everything else and report the one missing item plainly.
